<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-05-02"><hi rend="italic">May 2,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 173.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have been informed by the Venezuelan
                            Government that Dr. Jose de Jesus Paul has been appointed the
                            representative of Venezuela on the mixed commission which is to consider
                            the claims of the United States. Doctor Paul is also the Venezuelan
                            member of the mixed commission for the French claims.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William W.
                            Russell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>